<h3>Future level: 100 trillion, trillion.</h3>
<p >I bet you have seen the movie the fast and furious and Tron, because if you`re not, you`re not a fan of cars and tech, and you shouldn`t be bothering reading this blog. if you are, then imagine swapping one vehicle in both of the movie. Light cycle in a scene where the car evades the cop? I bet the vehicle just so stand out, I bet the police let them go first and wait for a call if anyone saw a vehicle that seems like a space ship. The heavy nissan GTR in light cycle match? well, the whole track is made out of glass apparently, good luck with the launch control.  If there is a bridge that can connect the best of both world, that would be this one; BMW i8.</p>

<p>well most of the time, before writing about cars, I would make some research first; the previous generation,design and power-train altogether combined.for the i8, it's just way too impossible. It's like describing the first generation of iPad, where there is no ancestor of it to make a reference. this car had just created a whole new class in a whole new level, ventured deeply into uncharted territories.

is this car, by any mean, comparable to any other standard model? lets try with the exotic Mercedes Benz SLR McLaren first, as both have door that opens in a really swag-manner. the merc have V8-punching piston, while the i8 shy away with its 3 inline pistons . Even BMW mini have a punching power more than the i8, but the latter can make a 0-60 sprint in about 3 - 4 seconds, twice as much needed for the cooper. the car literally just shying away for the big old monstrous engine and adapt new technologies in its construction process.

this is what the guys in Leipzig, Germany call 'BMW Concept Vision Efficient Dynamics'. I'm not sure if they speak english. In a more simpler term, it is called Hybrid. Super advance hybrid, as there are certain things that is not available in the standard Prius. </p>


