<p>We'll get to that later, but first, we'll start with it's most outrageous-Wow factor, which is exterior design. try stand in front of it, I bet you wouldn't shut your eyes for more than a minute.The v shaped front hood seems to be well integrated with the whole body structure. Well they don't want people to see its pony sized electric motor anyway. lower your a sight a bit, and you'll see the recgonizable twin hexagonal grille and a whole lot of  interconnected lines and curves making up those front grille and bumper. I gotta say, in my eyes the front bumper does looks like the spartan head shield. adding the final touch is definitely the headlight, matrix led light with thick accent of eyeliner underneath. 

if there is no BMW batch on the hood nor the wheel, I bet people would think that this car is made by aliens. Some bunch of aliens that had graduated from arts and engineering school. I bet those aliens just wanna keep the car as dope as it can, if not they wouldn’t bother making this grand door structure on the A pillar that split the differences between scissor and gull-wing door. I’m interested to know how would the car perform parking in a tight space at the grocery store.

students from engineering that had studied aerodynamic engineering would quickly recognize the reason behind all of this car structure, especially the v shaped clearance structure at the back of the car. some would relate it with Ferrari F12 Berlinetta which has the hollow intake and bridge structure at the front, reducing drag co efficiency(Cd), slippery up to 0.26.and the rear structure does looks as equally awesome as the front too, as the rear light resemble much of the front accent eyeline. Above all, I’d say the i8 is built for more of a social experience rather than getting you from A to B. try getting this car into gas station without attracting much attention. Even the police would stop you by to take some photos. </p>

